title: Wednesday Sector Laggards: Music & Electronics Stores, Railroads - Nasdaq.com
text: In trading on Wednesday, music & electronics stores shares were relative laggards, down on the day by about 2.4%. Helping drag down the group were shares of Gamestop, off about 12.3% and shares of Rent-a-center off about 3.4% on the day.    makeArticleAd();  Also lagging the market Wednesday are railroads shares, down on the day by about 0.9% as a group, led down by Canadian Pacific Railway, trading lower by about 1.8% and Norfolk Southern, trading lower by about 1.4%.
